snippet.title: The Great Emu War • Puppet History
snippet.description:
Welcome one and all to Puppet History Season 4!

Bloopers! Behind the scenes looks! Other exclusive content available at
http://www.patreon.com/watcher​

GET PUPPET HISTORY MERCH:
https://watcherstore.com/

Created and hosted by Shane Madej
Director: Katie LeBlanc
Featuring: Ryan Bergara, Kate Peterman
Writer: Garrett Werner
Editor: Anthony Frederick
Research: Kari Koeppel
Camera Operator: Karen Du
Sound Operator: TJ Marchbank
Production Assistant: Blake Benson
Motion Graphics Animators: Mike Fox, Julia Capuano
Graphic Artist: Mollie Ong
Additional Music By: Patrick Volker
Puppets by: Madison Girifalco (@mindovermadison)
Production Coordinator: Brittney Lee
Creative Director of Post Production: Anthony Frederick
Head of Development: Katie LeBlanc
Production Manager: Nicole Beaudoin
Executive Producers: Steven Lim, Shane Madej, Ryan Bergara

Music Provided by Audio Network
SFX by Audioblocks
Logo Designed by Jennet Liaw
Logo Sound Design by Yuta Endo (@yuuutaendo)

Image Credits:
Wheat, DataBase Center for Life Science (DBCLS), CC BY 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0, via Wikimedia Commons
Rockport Massachusetts, Rosapicci, CC BY-SA 4.0, via Wikimedia Commons
Free Public Landing sign in Turnchapel, Plymouth © Y.ssk / Wikimedia Commons
Commonwealth Bank of Australia one-pound note (1952). Image courtesy of Heritage Auctions, Public domain, via Wikimedia Commons
Commonwealth Bank of Australia ten-shilling note (1934). Image courtesy of Heritage Auctions, Public domain, via Wikimedia Commons
Commonwealth Bank of Australia ten-pound note (1954-59). Image courtesy of Heritage Auctions, Public domain, via Wikimedia Commons
Early 1900's residence in the community of New Rochelle, Westchester County, New York. NatGeoLover, CC BY-SA 4.0, via Wikimedia Commons
Thumbs up, John Sandbanks, CC BY-SA 4.0, via Wikimedia Commons
Sewing kit with embroidered edging, "CCBY" by Auckland Museum  
Locomotive 43106 departing from Highley Station, Tom Axford 1, CC BY-SA 4.0, via Wikimedia Commons
Western Railroad box car, Chris Light, CC BY-SA 4.0 via Wikimedia Commons
Outback South Australia, Brett Stanley, CC BY-SA 4.0, via Wikimedia Commons
Sunrise in Outback, Binskip Inskip, CC BY-SA 4.0 via Wikimedia Commons
German WW2 uniforms, Costică Axinte from România, Public domain, via Wikimedia Commons
M2 Browning, Cjp24, CC BY-SA 4.0, via Wikimedia Commons
Interior of Johnie's Coffee Shop, Downtowngal, CC BY-SA 4.0, via Wikimedia Commons
Арина Ахметова, CC BY-SA 4.0 via Wikimedia Commons
Green Tiled Pixel Art, JayTholen, CC BY-SA 4.0 via Wikimedia Commons
Computer game character Giuseppe Timberpen, pixel art: Katuenidea: Gebu, CC BY-SA 4.0, via Wikimedia Commons
Marlboro cigarettes, Santeri Viinamäki, CC BY-SA 4.0, via Wikimedia Commons
Meritorious Service Medal, Hsq7278, CC BY-SA 4.0, via Wikimedia Commons
Portrait of Ralph Spooner, Tribune staff photographer (copyright held by SEARCH foundation), CC BY 4.0 via Wikimedia Commons

We strive to accurately represent the historical period covered in this episode, but some creative liberties are taken based on available historical assets. 

Social:

https://www.facebook.com/watcherentertainment
https://wearewatcher.tumblr.com/

hello@watcherentertainment.com
